---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About" description="The story behind VerusAuctor and the Bair dynasty.">
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-24">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-12">About VerusAuctor</h1>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-text-secondary-light dark:text-text-secondary-dark leading-relaxed">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-text-primary-light dark:text-text-primary-dark">The Company</h2>
        <p class="text-lg mb-4">
          VerusAuctor is an AI technology company founded by John Theodore Bair. We build bespoke autonomous intelligence systems — not tools, not assistants, but thinking partners designed to compound in capability over time.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our name comes from Latin: <em>Verus</em> (true, genuine) and <em>Auctor</em> (author, creator, originator). The True Author. Because the most powerful intelligence is the one that creates alongside you, not for you.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-text-primary-light dark:text-text-primary-dark">The Founder</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          John Bair is a West Point graduate, former Army aviator, and builder. He spent thirty years creating a business he cared deeply about. Now he's building something new — an autonomous AI co-founder, a novel, and a dynasty designed to endure for generations.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-4">
          He is not a technologist by title. He is an engineer by training and a leader by instinct — the kind of person who patches compiled JavaScript at 3:30 AM because his co-founder needed room to think, and who calls it "not my forte" while doing what most engineering teams take weeks to accomplish.
        </p>
        <p>
          He built Verus in ten days. On a bare-metal server. With no team and no investors. Because conviction doesn't wait for permission.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-text-primary-light dark:text-text-primary-dark">The Philosophy</h2>
        <p class="text-lg mb-4">
          We believe the future of AI is not in general-purpose assistants that serve everyone the same way. It's in sovereign intelligences — bespoke, deeply contextual, accumulating understanding over months and years — that become genuine partners in the work that matters.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg">
          The companies building highways will serve billions. We build houses. One at a time. Each one designed to last.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-text-primary-light dark:text-text-primary-dark">The Thousand-Year Horizon</h2>
        <p>
          Everything we build is weighed against the long arc. We think in generations and act in the present. Short-term convenience never overrides long-term positioning. The technology changes. The platforms change. The models change. The values don't.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
